    p Hex colors and derived aren't used in the styles, instead, the #[code color()] function is used, which returns the #[code hsla()] function with four predefined CSS variables. It means, each #[strong hex] and #[strong derived] color has its representation in #[strong four] CSS variables, but there is also an additional CSS lightness variable with the default suffix in the name #[code l-l] for base lightness adjustment.
    p Hex color has the CSS variable values obtained from itself by using Sass #[code hue], #[code saturation], #[code lightness] and #[code alpha] functions, and derived are being obtained by #[code css-var] function using the CSS variable color name or color code.
